{
  "info": {
    "name": "Flight Ops API",
    "description": "Two folders:\n\n1. \"OpenSky API (direct)\" — calls OpenSky's own /states/all endpoint directly using the OAuth2 client-credentials flow, to verify your OpenSky credentials work independent of this backend.\n2. \"FlightOps API (local)\" — calls this project's own /aircraft endpoints. No auth required — this API authenticates to OpenSky internally; it does not require a bearer token from callers.\n\nSETUP:\n1. Collection ▸ Variables tab — set the CURRENT VALUE column (not just Initial) for `clientId` and `clientSecret` with your real OpenSky API client credentials. Both are typed `secret`, so they're masked in the UI, but note that Postman does NOT strip secret-type values from an exported collection file — don't commit real values into this file.\n2. `openSkyToken` is set automatically by the \"OpenSky API (direct)\" folder's pre-request script — it mints a fresh token before each request in that folder. You don't need to set it yourself.\n3. `baseUrl` defaults to this API's local HTTP profile (http://localhost:5273). If you run the HTTPS profile instead, either switch `baseUrl` to https://localhost:7173 or disable SSL certificate verification in Postman ▸ Settings (the dev cert is self-signed).\n4. `lamin`/`lomin`/`lamax`/`lomax` default to a bounding box over Switzerland — a commonly used OpenSky example region with reliably dense air traffic. `icao24` defaults to a real aircraft's address in valid 6-hex-character format.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "clientId", "value": "", "type": "secret" },
    { "key": "clientSecret", "value": "", "type": "secret" },
    { "key": "openSkyToken", "value": "", "type": "secret" },
    { "key": "openSkyTokenUrl", "value": "https://auth.opensky-network.org/auth/realms/opensky-network/protocol/openid-connect/token", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "openSkyApiBaseUrl", "value": "https://opensky-network.org/api", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "baseUrl", "value": "http://localhost:5273", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "lamin", "value": "45.8389", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "lomin", "value": "5.9962", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "lamax", "value": "47.8229", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "lomax", "value": "10.5226", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "icao24", "value": "3c6444", "type": "string" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "OpenSky API (direct)",
      "auth": {
        "type": "bearer",
        "bearer": [
          { "key": "token", "value": "{{openSkyToken}}", "type": "string" }
        ]
      },
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "prerequest",
          "script": {
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "exec": [
              "const clientId = pm.collectionVariables.get('clientId');",
              "const clientSecret = pm.collectionVariables.get('clientSecret');",
              "",
              "if (!clientId || !clientSecret) {",
              "  console.warn('clientId/clientSecret collection variables are empty — set them in the Variables tab (Current Value) before running requests in this folder.');",
              "}",
              "",
              "pm.sendRequest({",
              "  url: pm.collectionVariables.get('openSkyTokenUrl'),",
              "  method: 'POST',",
              "  header: { 'Content-Type': 'application/x-www-form-urlencoded' },",
              "  body: {",
              "    mode: 'urlencoded',",
              "    urlencoded: [",
              "      { key: 'grant_type', value: 'client_credentials' },",
              "      { key: 'client_id', value: clientId },",
              "      { key: 'client_secret', value: clientSecret }",
              "    ]",
              "  }",
              "}, (err, res) => {",
              "  if (err) { console.error(err); return; }",
              "  pm.collectionVariables.set('openSkyToken', res.json().access_token);",
              "});"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Get States (bounding box)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{openSkyApiBaseUrl}}/states/all?lamin={{lamin}}&lomin={{lomin}}&lamax={{lamax}}&lomax={{lomax}}",
              "host": ["{{openSkyApiBaseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["states", "all"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "lamin", "value": "{{lamin}}" },
                { "key": "lomin", "value": "{{lomin}}" },
                { "key": "lamax", "value": "{{lamax}}" },
                { "key": "lomax", "value": "{{lomax}}" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Direct call to OpenSky's /states/all for the default bbox. Expect 200 with a `states` array. This costs OpenSky quota — see the design doc for the credit-cost rules."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get States (single icao24)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{openSkyApiBaseUrl}}/states/all?icao24={{icao24}}",
              "host": ["{{openSkyApiBaseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["states", "all"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "icao24", "value": "{{icao24}}" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Direct call to OpenSky for a single aircraft. Expect 200 with `states` either containing one entry (if currently airborne/tracked) or null."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "FlightOps API (local)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Get Aircraft Snapshot (valid bbox)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/aircraft?lamin={{lamin}}&lomin={{lomin}}&lamax={{lamax}}&lomax={{lomax}}",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["aircraft"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "lamin", "value": "{{lamin}}" },
                { "key": "lomin", "value": "{{lomin}}" },
                { "key": "lamax", "value": "{{lamax}}" },
                { "key": "lomax", "value": "{{lomax}}" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Expect 200 with an AircraftSnapshot body ({ aircraft: [...], stale: false }). Backed by DirectSnapshotProvider or CachedSnapshotProvider depending on the OpenSky:RateLimitAware setting."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Aircraft Snapshot (invalid bbox → 400)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/aircraft?lamin=20&lomin=10&lamax=10&lomax=20",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["aircraft"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "lamin", "value": "20" },
                { "key": "lomin", "value": "10" },
                { "key": "lamax", "value": "10" },
                { "key": "lomax", "value": "20" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "lamin > lamax — an inverted box. Expect 400 with a ValidationProblem body from FluentValidation."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Aircraft Detail (valid icao24)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/aircraft/{{icao24}}",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["aircraft", "{{icao24}}"]
            },
            "description": "Expect 200 with the aircraft's current state if tracked, otherwise 404 (still a valid-format icao24, just not currently airborne)."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Aircraft Detail (invalid format → 400)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/aircraft/not-a-valid-icao",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["aircraft", "not-a-valid-icao"]
            },
            "description": "Not a 6-character hex address. Expect 400 with a ValidationProblem body — rejected before any call to OpenSky."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Aircraft Detail (unknown icao24 → 404)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/aircraft/ffffff",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["aircraft", "ffffff"]
            },
            "description": "Valid 6-hex-character format but not a real/tracked aircraft. Expect 404."
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
